==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Siderite
<hw>Sid"er*ite</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>sideritis</ets>
loadstone, Gr. <?/<?/<?/<?/, <?/<?/<?/<?/, of iron, from <?/<?/<?/<?/
iron.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Carbonate
of iron, an important ore of iron occurring generally in cleavable
masses, but also in rhombohedral crystals. It is of a light yellowish
brown color. Called also <altname>sparry iron</altname>,
<altname>spathic iron</altname>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A meteorite
consisting solely of metallic iron.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>An
indigo-blue variety of quartz.</def> <sd>(d)</sd> <def>Formerly,
magnetic iron ore, or loadstone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Any plant of the genus
<gen>Sideritis</gen>; ironwort.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

